Responsibilities

Perform troubleshooting and provide day-to-day support including hardware, software, end-user and helpdesk;
Perform hardware installation, configuration or maintenance, including PC, notebook, Mac, server, printer and other computer peripheral devices;
Conduct software installation, configuration or maintenance including MS-Office, Outlook, Windows, Mac, Adobe products, AntiVirus and other office applications;
Provide regular testing of IT equipment and monitoring of IT equipment status and ah hoc on site support;

Requirements

IVE/Diploma holder in Information System, Computer Science, Computer Engineering or related disciplines;
1 year experience in IT technical / deskside support will be an advantage, fresh graduates are also welcomed;
Knowledge in Windows;
Knowledge in AD, DNS, FTP, TCP/IP, POP3, SMTP & SNMP;
Good computer knowledge of MS-Word, Excel, PowerPoint;
Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese
Immediately available will be an advantage

We offer excellent career development opportunities to unleash your potential, competitive remuneration package including a 5-day work week, medical insurance & dental plan, discretionary bonus, staff training and staff purchasing discount etc.


Interest parties, please simply click "Apply now" to submit your application with full resume stating current & expected salary and the availability for reporting duty. 

You are welcome to visit our website to know more about us: www.popular.com.hk or http://ephhk.popularworldhk.com.


Personal data provided by job applicants will be kept strictly confidential and will be used solely for employment related purpose.  Only short-listed candidates will be contacted.

This is a Yearly Renewable Contract Position. (Service Provider: Manpower). As a global ICT company with a presence in over 170 countries and regions, we provide a broad platform where employees can realize their personal value. This is an excellent opportunity to build up your career in ICT industry where you be enriched with our Huawei innovative business solutions.

Responsibilities:

- Be responsible for customer requirements and demand plans of key projects by supporting the operation of comprehensive plans;
- Organize project and assist supply chain managers to participate in project bidding;
- Identify supply requirement risks and make supply solutions accordingly;
- Monitor the fulfillment of contracts and key projects and resolve abnormal cases to ensure the goods supplied timely and accurately.

Requirements:

- Bachelor Degree or above in procurement and/ or supply chain management or other related disciplines;
- Basic understanding on general software knowledge and equipped with excellent IT and MS software skills; 
- Strong interpersonal and communication skills, ability to establish and maintain cooperative and harmonious working relationship within a multicultural work environment;
- Ability to work in a team and build up good relations with all projects stakeholders;
- With integrated decision-making skills, ability to prioritize and focus;
- To be positive and have that "never give up and work under pressure" attitudes;
- Good Command of written and spoken English and Cantonese. Knowledge of Mandarin is an advantage.

Experienced candidates will be considered as specialist position

Responsibilities:

Responsible for the requirements gathering, system analysis, design and development of the back office system as well as customer online platform and mobile applications;
Provide technical solution in the enterprise architecture design and implementation;
Perform proof-of-concepts of technical solution;
Prepare the technical specification and related documents;
Ensure to follow the coding standard and best practices;
Perform and ensure the quality of unit tests and system integration tests;
Provide ongoing application maintenance and program refinement; and
Support ad-hoc tasks on demand.

Requirements:

A Bachelor’s Degree in Information Technology, Computer Science or related disciplines;
At least 2 years’ working experience.  Fresh graduates are welcome and may be considered as Software Developer;
Experience in software development for backend, frontend, server-side, API web services, cloud based and mobile applications development, maintenance and support;
Hands-on programming skills in web development with PHP, Java, JavaScript, CSS, programming frameworks including Drupal, JASON, XML, WordPress & Microsoft .NET framework;
Knowledge and/or Experience of Database programming and both SQL/T-SQL and NoSQL (MS-SQL, MySQL);
Experience in preparing system integration, data migration, and rollout plan, providing IT security requirements and issues;
Experience in performing the stress test and optimizing the system performance;
Experience in managing vendors would be an advantage;
Experience in using Apache, Tomcat, Git and/or TortoiseSVN, Jenkins development services or tools would be an advantage;
Mature, proactive, flexible, self-motivated and team oriented;
Possesses analytical, problem solving and interpersonal skills;
Willing to learn and improve skills;
Willing to explore and study the new technologies applicable to new projects;
Good communication and documentation skills; and
Proficiency in both written and spoken English and Chinese.


Please send full resume with expected salary and reference no. quoted to Haven of Hope Christian Service, Staff Engagement Department, 7 Haven of Hope Road, Tseung Kwan O, New Territories or via email by clicking "Apply Now", or via Whatsapp no. 6507 8148 (with reference no. quoted at the caption) on or before 5 February 2022. Only short-listed candidates will be notified.
Enquiry: 2703 3227 (Phone); 6507 8148 (Whatsapp).
For details about our organization, please visit www.hohcs.org.hk.
