Duties: The appointees will be responsible for the development and support of core IT application systems.

Requirements:

A Bachelor’s Degree / Associate Degree / Higher Diploma in Information Technology, Computer Science or related disciplines;
At least two years’ working experience in application system development or support services;
Hands-on experience with web application development and PL/SQL programming;
Knowledge in web-based system design and application security definitely an advantage;
Good oral and written communication skills in both Chinese and English; and
High-calibre fresh graduates are also welcome.

Employment Terms:  The remuneration package will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.  Appointment will be on a fixed-term contract with contract-end-gratuity, MPF benefits, medical and dental care.  Future employment may be offered on renewable contracts subject to performance and staffing needs.

Date for Application Review: 7 February 2022

Applications would be considered until the post is filled.

Application forms can be obtained from the HKEAA office on 13/F., Southorn Centre, 130 Hennessy Road, Wan Chai, Hong Kong or downloaded from the HKEAA website (www.hkeaa.edu.hk/tc/Career/general.html).  Completed application forms should be returned to the Manager – Human Resources at the above address. Due to the secrecy nature of HKEAA's job duties, applicants invited for interview may be required to make a declaration of any conflict of interests. Applicants not notified within 10 weeks from the application review date should consider their applications unsuccessful.

The HKEAA is an equal opportunities employer and welcomes applications from all qualified candidates. Information provided relating to employment will be kept confidential and used only for processing applications. For details, please refer to the Policy Statement on Equal Opportunities and the Personal Information Collection Statement on the HKEAA website (www.hkeaa.edu.hk).

Responsibilities

Working closely with PM, Designers, Developers and Programmers
Understand the client's requirements and generate technical solutions
Identify issues and implement solutions to complex problems
Perform function enhancement, system deployment and testing

Requirements


Higher Diploma / Bachelor Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or any related disciplines;
1 year or above experience in web or application development;
Experience in PHP framework (e.g. Laravel, Codeigniter), MySql, MSSQL, RESTful API, HTML, CSS, JavaScript framework (e.g. React, bootstrap), Python will be an advantage;
Experience in payment integration (e.g. Paypal / Stripe) will be an advantage;
Good team player with strong analytical and problem-solving skills;
Self-motivated with can do attitude and timely delivery results
Working Location in Tsuen Wan

Nice to have

Experience in cloud storage, deployment and computing. We use Azure / AWS but we're open to other platform experience

Autotoll is Hong Kong's major Intelligent Transport and Smart City solution provider, as well as being a financial institution with Stored Value Facility License and a Faster Payment System Participant, providing the best solutions and efficient services to our corporate and consumer customers.

With the constant evolution of our innovative solutions, agility is an integral part of our development process.  We are looking for a Solutions Architect as part of the team to assist in new projects and drive the transformation of existing systems.  If you are interested in developing industry leading solutions, Autotoll is a great place to grow your career and be part of our winning team.


About The Role:

Be part of the dynamic team of developers and engineers building modern, robust, DevOps infrastructures;
Involve in the all aspects of Autotoll’s Smart Solution strategy from solutions development, bid management, Smart City projects initiation and delivery;
Develop end-to-end technology solutions, system architectural design, solution planning, and feasibility study, create technical write ups, scope of work and presentations for proposals and provides input to contract and SLA;
Lead technical discussion with peer architects, developers and project managers to validate design and derive fit-for-purpose solution;
Lead the effort in new technology evaluation and onboarding, followed by establishing new standards, best practices and guidelines;
Automate everything in the application lifecycle from design, setup, test, release, update, support, and improve.

About You

Positive attitude and a strong commitment to delivering quality work;
Experience in leading a team of subject matter expert and delivery management;
Solid architecture experience in DevOps, CI/CD, process automation and application performance monitoring;
Sound knowledge with scalable infrastructure architecture including cloud solutions, operating systems, networking, security, backups and monitoring;
Bachelor's degree or above in Computing or related discipline;
Minimum 5 years of experience in IT architecture design for large-scale enterprises.

What you can get from us:
On-the-job training, learning and development provided
Executive workshops, interest class, corporate purchase discount offered by SHKP
Competitive salary and annual leaves
Flexible working opportunities
Interested parties, please send full resume with expected salary and available date to Human Resources and Administration Department by e-mail or by fax 2111 9459.
(Data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.)

Our client is one of the largest online shopping ecommerce platforms in Hong Kong. They are looking for new team members to join their data science teams.  

Data Analysts / Senior Data Analysts / Trainee Analysts

20K (entry levels) to around 60K (senior levels)


Responsibilities:

Agile team collaboration in continual development of Company's big data analytics platform and existing data governance frameworks
Data analysis, data discovery and metadata management for business intelligence (BI), quantitative modeling, machine learning and predictive analytics projects
Data warehousing, data mining and extract/transform/load (ETL) integration in cloud and on-premise environments
Data visualization, BI reporting, data dashboard design & development
Requirements:

Degree holder in IT and data sciences related subjects
Over or around 3 years of technical experience in data analytics, business intelligence (BI), data warehousing, or related functional areas
Good knowledge of major data programming languages and analytic tools such as Python, Hadoop, Tableau, MS SQL, Oracle RDBMS, PL SQL, Azure Cloud, Microsoft Power BI, Excel Power Query, Google Analytics, Google Data Studio highly preferred
Fluent Chinese and English communication with local team members
More experience will be considered as Assistant Manager (Data Analysis)
Less experience or Fresh will also consider for junior post

Customer Data Analyst (SAS)

Your role:

Develop Dashboards to facilitate efficient data analysis for product performance, customer profiles and campaign effectiveness;
Conduct quantitative analysis and data mining to support management decisions and provide data-driven recommendations;
Organize and prepare regular reports relating to business performance and service usage;
Conduct user acceptance test of in-house-developed applications.

To succeed in this role

University graduate in Computer Science, Information Technology, Data Science, Statistics or relevant discipline;
1 – 4 years’ relevant experience, preferably in data analysis, database programming or database management
Proficient in SAS, SQL, Python or other data mining tools;
Practical experience in data visualization tools (e.g. Qlik View/Sense, Power BI or Tableau);
Good analytical and problem solving skills, able to work under tight timeline;
Self-motivated and able to accomplish multiple tasks with minimal supervision;
Good interpersonal and communication skills and able to work with people at all levels;
Good command in both spoken and written English;
Candidate with more experience will be considered for the position of Senior Customer Data Analyst.
